1
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:04,360
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:07,880
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:10,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,680
I'm here to help you. Hurry, get out.

5
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:18,280
<i>What did you say? The women escaped?</i>

6
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:21,080
Damn it. What am I supposed to do now?

7
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,000
What's wrong with you?

8
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,040
Kicking hard again. And again.

9
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,160
<i>Boss gives you 48 hours.</i>

10
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,840
Find the mole in your place.

11
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,360
<i>That alone is enough</i>
<i>to turn Natee into complete mush.</i>

12
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:50,520
<i>There are also the account records showing</i>
<i>money transferred from the government.</i>

13
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,160
<i>And the photos I deep-faked</i>

14
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,720
<i>that he's in contact with the government.</i>

15
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,880
I'm screwed.

16
00:03:57,200 --> 00:04:02,440
All the data will make Natee look like
a top-tier mole inside the network.

17
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:05,880
And just now,
I uploaded everything to the dark web.

18
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:10,560
And faked unencrypted
data-trading conversations.

19
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,800
In just a few minutes,

20
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,960
the criminals who prowl
the dark web for information will…

21
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,160
find it.

22
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,480
So that means

23
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:24,080
Phoenix will find out soon
that Natee is the mole.

24
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:27,240
After that,
we'll see what Natee decides to do.

25
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:46,840
I won't let myself become a pawn
for you to parade around for credit.

26
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:16,400
We couldn't find him.
He probably managed to escape.

27
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,600
He couldn't have gone far.

28
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,760
If I'm still here,

29
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,080
no one escapes from Pha Mok.

30
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:30,000
The ones causing trouble for us and Natee

31
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:34,040
are moles working with the government.

32
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:37,680
Once they were exposed, they tried
to blackmail us with the Death File.

33
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,840
It's the data that can lead to Boss.

34
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,960
Death File?

35
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,920
Data that can lead to Boss?

36
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,720
Boss trusts him deeply.

37
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:55,040
So he has a lot of information on
the trafficking network.

38
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,240
But don't worry.

39
00:05:57,520 --> 00:06:00,760
Arab is hunting them down.
They can't escape.

40
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,880
Those backstabbing dogs.

41
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,680
What?

42
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,080
- Death File?
- Yes.

43
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:17,000
A crucial file that can expose
and rip off Phoenix's mask.

44
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,160
But if you reach Natee
later than Arab Dammoh,

45
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:24,640
the gunman who attacked you that day
and is now hunting Natee,

46
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,640
we'll lose the chance
to get the Death File.

47
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:31,640
So if we get this file,
we can end the game completely, right?

48
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,720
Perfect timing. Moh and I
are already tracking that gunman.

49
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:40,920
Thanks so much for the great intel, babe.

50
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,920
Hey. Enough messing around.

51
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:53,720
It's our time now, Moh.

52
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,440
Just the two of us left. Let's move.

53
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,840
It stinks, Sarge.

54
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,680
What stinks? Someone else's leftovers?

55
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,520
- Ms. Mook, calm down please.
- Let go.

56
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,480
- Ms. Mook, please. Stop.
- Let go. I said let go!

57
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,320
- Let go.
- Mook. Enough. Stop it.

58
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,880
You're the one who needs to stop.

59
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,640
You can't force me
to stay locked in here forever.

60
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,000
How many times do I have to repeat myself

61
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:23,440
why this is necessary!

62
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,280
That's your problem.

63
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:28,400
You created this mess.
You never listen to anyone.

64
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,160
But the ones who suffer are me and Mom.

65
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,440
Mook.

66
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,920
Boss.

67
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,240
Please take care of her.

68
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,640
I'm not a prisoner.

69
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,480
I promise.

70
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:07,120
I won't let them come in
and make you uncomfortable again.

71
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,440
But your father
is still very worried about you.

72
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:16,000
So you'll have to stay
within my sight at all times.

73
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,840
Is that better?

74
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,480
It's fine.

75
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:26,600
Anyway, my relationship with your father

76
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,520
only seems to make you uncomfortable.

77
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,080
I'm not trying to replace your mother.

78
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,280
Do not talk about my mom.

79
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:44,200
If you've really lived life as an adult,

80
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,600
you'd know

81
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:50,840
that for men, love alone is not enough.

82
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,080
Love alone isn't enough?

83
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,200
Just like they say.

84
00:08:57,280 --> 00:09:01,160
People with matching morals
tend to attract each other.

85
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,000
So this is how it is.

86
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:09,600
We're adults now. I think speaking
directly is easier to understand.

87
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,000
Okay.

88
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,240
I'm sorry.

89
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,760
I understand how you feel now.

90
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,880
You want to see your mother
at the hospital?

91
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,240
I can take you there.

92
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:42,040
But only if I go with you.
Otherwise, your father won't agree.

93
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,280
So what do we do now, Sarge?

94
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:03,800
There are these guys and those guys.
Should we call for backup?

95
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:09,080
If we wait for backup
and Natee gets killed first,

96
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:11,600
the Death File will be gone.

97
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,560
So what's your call?

98
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:18,440
- Where is he now?
- He's into the forest to cross the border.

99
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,120
There are armed villagers escorting him.

100
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,400
He's probably fleeing across the border.

101
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,200
Those three small fry are yours.

102
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,240
Arab is mine.

103
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:33,200
Are you insane, Sarge?

104
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:35,320
Three of them and just me?
Can I handle that?

105
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,640
Hey.

106
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:40,000
There's nothing Sai Pradit Technical
guys like us can't do.

107
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,560
And if you don't make it,

108
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:44,960
I'll tell your family
that you're a national hero.

109
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,200
Hey!

110
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,040
- I love you.
- I can't, Sarge.

111
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,480
Go handle it.

112
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,960
Let's go.

113
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,680
Sarge.

114
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,800
Oh? Great. And you say you love me.

115
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,400
I'd better love myself right now.

116
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,080
Sarge, seriously.

117
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:26,280
If I survive, I'll kill you.

118
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,600
Hey. Let's take a break.

119
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,560
Hey. We can't stop.

120
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:18,840
I paid you to get me across. Keep going.

121
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,560
I know who you're running from.

122
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,560
- What the hell? You want trouble?
- You messing with me?

123
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,200
Damn.

124
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:30,880
Calm down.

125
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:36,400
I get it. You don't want
to get targeted by Pha Mok.

126
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,440
But I promise.

127
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,560
If you help me cross,

128
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,480
you can take all the money in my bag.

129
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,560
Think about it.

130
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:49,240
Just a few more kilometers
and I'll be across.

131
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,960
And then what? You'll all be filthy rich.

132
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,320
Who the hell are you?

133
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,880
Choose.

134
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,200
Come with me,

135
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,320
or stay here and wait
for Arab to blow your head off.

136
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,320
You're one of those who attacked me.

137
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,880
Go with me and you live.

138
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:47,200
Stay here and

139
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:51,080
Arab will torture you
until you hand over the Death File.

140
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,240
You know about the Death File.

141
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,280
So it's true, just like Arab suspected.

142
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:59,040
One of you is the mole.

143
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,040
I only threatened the Death File
with Tiangmon.

144
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,240
If this leaked, that means…

145
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,320
Ratee is the mole.

146
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,960
You figured it out just now. Good.

147
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,240
I'm the only one who can help you survive.

148
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,880
Come with me. Hand over the Death File.

149
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,640
The government
will protect you as a witness.

150
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:27,240
- Go. Help me. Go.
- Go.

151
00:15:15,880 --> 00:15:17,160
Why did you pull the pin?

152
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:19,360
Right. I forgot.

153
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,280
Moh.

154
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,560
Looks like I'm not the only one
who got played by Arab.

155
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:32,240
Come here.

156
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,480
If Ratee really is a mole, that means

157
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:41,520
she's with the same group
Boss ordered me to get rid of.

158
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,440
She survived and stayed undercover.

159
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,880
You still call Phoenix "boss"?

160
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:52,000
Even after he sent a gunman to hunt you
just because you screwed up once?

161
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:56,160
- It's because you staged this to frame me.
- I didn't stage it.

162
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,760
But you only stay together
for the benefits.

163
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:01,240
I just poked your jealousy a bit,
and you started tearing each other apart.

164
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:07,440
Don't think my boss is stupid.
And don't think Ratee can survive forever.

165
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:10,000
The moment she slips up, I guarantee

166
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,120
she'll be tortured
until she begs for her life.

167
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:16,560
Don't get smart with the person
who's trying to save you.

168
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,520
Where's the Death File.

169
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,920
Ouch. Okay, okay. I swear.

170
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:24,840
‪Okay.

171
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,560
You'll get to see my trick shot too.

172
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,640
If you save my life,

173
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,240
I'll hand the Death File over to…

174
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:59,200
Natee. Natee. Don't die yet.

175
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,160
Help… Help me.

176
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:07,599
All right, I'll help you.
Where did you put the Death File?

177
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:12,440
The Death… File…

178
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,720
It's not with me.

179
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:19,400
You didn't keep it on you?
Hey. Natee. Where's the Death File?

180
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:44,520
Looks like I really can't
make friends with you after all.

181
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,640
But that's fine.

182
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,240
Soon, we probably
won't see each other again.

183
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,480
Since you'll likely
be following your mother.

184
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:56,360
What do you mean? Where am
I supposed to follow my mother to?

185
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,320
I thought
you already heard from the doctor.

186
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,640
About what?

187
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,760
Say it.

188
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:15,520
Your father is moving your mother
to England for treatment.

189
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:17,840
That's not true.

190
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:21,480
My mom already told my dad
not to move her anywhere.

191
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,840
Your father means well.

192
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:27,000
Staying here, her condition
will only stabilize or worsen.

193
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:29,320
Over there, there are
better doctors to treat her.

194
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:34,240
More like he wants to get rid of my mom.

195
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:39,720
So you and my dad can make
a fool of her more conveniently.

196
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:58,800
Let's go.

197
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:03,840
Hey.

198
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:06,600
Miss, move that way.

199
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,000
Come on. Follow me.

200
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:24,920
Ms. Mookda, hurry and get away.
This place is dangerous.

201
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:27,000
Go that way.

202
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,120
Thanks. Hey!

203
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:03,320
That's enough…

204
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,520
Hey!

205
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,760
Today is your day to die.

206
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,720
So how is he? Is he dead yet?

207
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,240
He can't die.

208
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,520
I need a witness to confirm everything.
Or Tiangmon will suspect me.

209
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,400
The Death File.

210
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:54,760
Natee didn't keep it on him.
He left it with someone.

211
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:57,480
He was about to tell me, then he died.

212
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,200
So you just watched him die
and came back empty-handed.

213
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,440
You don't get it. Haven you seen movies?

214
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:04,720
When the villain is about to talk

215
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,160
and then just dies.

216
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:11,320
I've already taken enough risks.
And wasted time too.

217
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,560
And I still don't know…

218
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:19,040
I still don't know where Moh is.
I don't know if he's dead or not.

219
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:20,480
How do you even lead the team?

220
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:24,200
If it weren't for that gunman in uniform,
I'd have handled it already.

221
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:27,720
I had to take risks
and I even lost one of my men.

222
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,760
But at least

223
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:33,960
the plan to have Dan gather intel
from Ms. Mookda can still move forward.

224
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,360
Hey. What are you doing?

225
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:42,120
For realism. I need to look
seriously injured from this attack.

226
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,440
Hey. You want me to shoot you?

227
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:46,600
Are you crazy? I can't shoot you.

228
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,720
I didn't say shoot.
Hit me in the face with the gun. Here.

229
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:51,800
Come on.

230
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,200
Hit you with the gun?

231
00:21:56,520 --> 00:22:00,760
I don't think that looks very realistic.
Someone like you needs something like…

232
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,840
Where are you going? Come here. Headlock!

233
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:10,960
You damn nagging woman.

234
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,920
Not even married yet and already
ordering this and that nonstop.

235
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,120
Make your ear tear off.

236
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,080
That way Tiangmon won't suspect anything.
One ear is enough.

237
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:19,720
You nagging woman.

238
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:21,880
Not even married
and already bossing around.

239
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:24,920
- Sarge. Sarge!
- If married, you'd order me to do laundry.

240
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,000
What are you doing?

241
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,440
I have to rehearse.

242
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:34,560
I'll do it properly
so Tiangmon won't suspect you. Come on.

243
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:44,600
In your dreams. You want payback on me?
I'll let those two handle it.

244
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:48,840
I'll kiss you.

245
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,200
Loud as a war drum.

246
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,400
Off to the underworld you go.

247
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,920
- Ms. Mook.
- Mr. Dan?

248
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,760
Ms. Mook.

249
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:52,640
Damn. That's messed up.

250
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,320
What the hell are you doing?

251
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,320
I'm asking what the hell you're doing!

252
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:05,840
If it's not realistic,
how would she trust you?

253
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,520
That was real ammo?

254
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,360
You used real bullets?

255
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,680
Why the hell did you use real bullets?

256
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,880
Why did you use them? I'm asking you why.

257
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:26,600
Did you even listen to the briefing?

258
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:33,080
If you don't push it to the limit,
like a trial from the Bu-Tueng sect,

259
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,240
how will she see your true nature.

260
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:38,200
And what if she got hit by a stray bullet
and died?

261
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,680
What would you do?!

262
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,280
I'm asking you!

263
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:45,080
If you can't separate real life
from fiction,

264
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,520
you shouldn't be working with us!

265
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:49,280
Why are you working with me?
Why are you even here?

266
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,480
Stop, Dan.

267
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,760
- Dan.
- Let go.

268
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:55,400
I told you to let go!

269
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,800
- What the hell's wrong with you?
- Me? This bastard is crazy!

270
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:06,640
If you can't separate
real life from fiction,

271
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:09,440
you shouldn't work.
You should be in a mental ward.

272
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:12,840
Tell Sarge and Ms. Duangnet this for me.

273
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,440
If he's here, I'm not.

274
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,360
Boss.

275
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,560
There's no trace at all.

276
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:02,400
Then why did you come back

277
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,680
if you still haven't found my daughter?

278
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,720
<i>Dad. It's me. Mook.</i>

279
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:16,720
Mook.

280
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:18,880
Are you safe?

281
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:22,320
I'm safe, Dad. You don't have to worry.

282
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:25,120
Mook, where are you hiding?

283
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:27,880
Tell me. I'll come get you right away.

284
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,320
You don't need to know.

285
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,640
Just know that I'm safe.

286
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:35,640
So you won't go around causing trouble
for other people just to look for me.

287
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:39,360
- Mook.
- <i>That's all, Dad.</i>

288
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:41,560
<i>Maybe, if you can't control me,</i>

289
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:44,400
it might make you realize

290
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:46,720
that between me and your work,

291
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:48,200
which one is more important.

292
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,760
Is that really a good idea?

293
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,080
It looks like your father
is very worried about you.

294
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:02,320
Mr. Dan, you don't know
what my father is like.

295
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,360
If he doesn't know
whether I'm alive or dead,

296
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:09,680
he'll definitely cause trouble for others.
He's never cared about anyone.

297
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,840
But he cares about you.

298
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:17,880
But everything he gives me,
I never wanted.

299
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,680
I just want to live happily.

300
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,720
No suspicion.
Without constantly being on guard.

301
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,640
That's all.

302
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:34,600
I don't have much time left.

303
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:38,640
I want to spend what time I have
as happily as possible.

304
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:42,320
I want to keep good memories.

305
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,480
Is that okay?

306
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:51,520
Really?

307
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,840
I saw Natee's body.

308
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,960
So we were called here.

309
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,680
Now Tiangmon is starting to trust no one.

310
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,440
Yes.

311
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:07,720
Because proving loyalty
is what Boss wants right now.

312
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:12,800
But Beauty and I have always worked
for Boss with absolute loyalty.

313
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:14,600
Natee said the same thing.

314
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:17,360
But when cornered,

315
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:20,160
he tried to use
the Death File to destroy Boss.

316
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,880
The Death File is gone.

317
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,600
But we can still be sure

318
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:29,800
they didn't get it.

319
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:32,800
Because my daughter was kidnapped,

320
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:37,840
and the Death File hasn't been used
to strike at Boss yet.

321
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:41,720
So where's the Death File now?

322
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:45,320
With someone Natee trusted.

323
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:48,280
It could be one of you two.

324
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:52,880
Or it could be someone else entirely.

325
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:56,840
Natee's death

326
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,680
made whoever has the file afraid to act.

327
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:06,080
But hunting them down
and protecting Boss's network interests

328
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,240
is the top priority.

329
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:10,560
We're fully ready to help.

330
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,600
Thank you very much.

331
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:15,640
How many years have you been working now?

332
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,480
About the same time as me?

333
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,160
No wonder Boss trusts you

334
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:24,080
to oversee the entire
financial network of Pha Mok.

335
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:28,880
But you…

336
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:32,120
still have to prove your loyalty.

337
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,680
So we don't repeat Natee's mistake.

338
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:41,800
Why are you grabbing me? Let go.

339
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,120
- Let go.
- Come here.

340
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:46,080
Hey. I didn't betray Boss.

341
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,800
It's just questioning.

342
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:52,200
If she's confident she's not a traitor,

343
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,360
there's nothing to worry about.

344
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:59,520
Open the door for me.

345
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:02,480
Open the door.

346
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:09,120
Open the door.

347
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:15,600
Okay. You probably
already know everything now.

348
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:18,040
I get that you're scared.

349
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:21,120
But I'm not here to drag you down with me.

350
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:30,840
This is the Death File.

351
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:34,480
Everything needed
to expose Boss is in here.

352
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,160
If I kept it on me,

353
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,840
I'd have no leverage against them.

354
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:43,680
Arab and Tiangmon don't listen to anyone.

355
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,840
They've never seen us as equals.

356
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,920
Right now,
you're the only one I can trust.

357
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:04,040
Keep it safe.

358
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,120
It'll be useful to protect us.

359
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:39,520
<i>If you can't separate</i>
<i>real life from fiction,</i>

360
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:42,440
you shouldn't work.
You should be in a mental ward.

361
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:45,840
Tell Sarge and Ms. Duangnet this for me.

362
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,280
If he's here, I'm not.

363
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,120
Dan is crazy about women.

364
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,840
He just sleeps with anyone.

365
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,960
That's why he got kicked out of service.

366
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,600
But what he said isn't wrong.

367
00:33:08,640 --> 00:33:10,440
Someone messed up like me

368
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:13,240
doesn't deserve a second chance.

369
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:15,840
I should be in a hospital instead.

370
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,640
You know that, huh?

371
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:29,880
Well. Sometimes you're so messed up…

372
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:32,000
What happened to you?

373
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,160
My own team betrayed me.

374
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,840
They were afraid

375
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:41,280
I'd expose their corruption
with drug dealers.

376
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,160
So they lured me into a trap.

377
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,960
Back then,

378
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:50,040
even the doctors gave up.
They thought I wouldn't survive.

379
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,720
Severe head trauma.

380
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:54,920
Wow, everyone on my team…

381
00:33:58,120 --> 00:33:59,440
Where's Sarge?

382
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:02,480
Moh. Moh.

383
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,200
Moh.

384
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,120
‪Let me see.

385
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,960
Shit. Where did you crawl out from?

386
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:12,000
Tell me.

387
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:14,199
Where's Sergeant Dab?

388
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:19,040
I'm going to kill him.

389
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:34,719
Moh.

390
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:40,040
Sarge.

391
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:43,159
Hey. Moh. You're alive?
I was just about to go help you…

392
00:34:43,239 --> 00:34:44,600
- Moh. Moh.
- Moh!

393
00:34:44,679 --> 00:34:46,080
- Moh. Stop.
- I'm still here!

394
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,679
- What the hell, Moh?
- Moh.

395
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:52,400
What do you think I am? Huh?!

396
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:55,800
A dog carrying a bone,
bringing it to you like that?

397
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:57,080
Isn't that what you are?

398
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:00,000
I'm the leader.

399
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:03,960
You're the subordinate.
If I order something, you do it.

400
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,280
Let go of me.

401
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:08,320
But you had no plan at all.

402
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:10,000
You sent me to die.
Do you even realize that?

403
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:11,960
- Really, Moh?
- Yeah!

404
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,040
Those three small fry are yours.

405
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:18,960
Arab is mine.

406
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:20,240
Hey!

407
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:22,040
- I love you.
- I can't, Sarge.

408
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:27,040
Why did you pull the pin?

409
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,240
Right. I forgot.

410
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:39,200
Sarge.

411
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:41,960
Was what Moh said true?

412
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:47,240
If it's true, so what?

413
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:50,560
Look at my face.

414
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:52,320
Do I look like your mom?

415
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,280
I'm not your mom.

416
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:59,120
I'm not here to comfort you
every time you come back injured.

417
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:02,320
Are you blind or something? Are you crazy?

418
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,120
I'm so disappointed in you.

419
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,480
You know what, Sarge?

420
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,080
We followed your lead

421
00:36:11,120 --> 00:36:12,760
because we believed
you'd get us out alive!

422
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:15,440
Don't be an idiot.

423
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:22,560
No matter how much I comfort you,
or baby you, it won't save you.

424
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:25,040
If you can't handle a mission like this,

425
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:27,720
if you're that scared,

426
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,560
go home and hide under your mom's skirt.

427
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:30,720
Let go of me!

428
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,760
- Sarge, let go.
- Get out.

429
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:35,280
You want your friend to die?

430
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:41,040
Listen to me. On the battlefield,

431
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:45,960
if you don't know how to love yourself,
no one else will love you.

432
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:48,560
- You'll all die anyway.
- Oh.

433
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:52,160
So all those subordinates who died
died because you were selfish, right?

434
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:55,680
- That's too much, you bastard.
- Sarge!

435
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,680
- Stop, Sarge.
- Stay out of this.

436
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:03,600
I'm so damn disappointed in you, Sarge.

437
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:13,560
- Sarge.
- Hey, hey.

438
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:17,880
What's going on?

439
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,800
Nothing.

440
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:23,560
And where did you two disappear to?
Kla. You again.

441
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:27,360
You're late because you were
fooling around with these girls, right?

442
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:28,680
Hey, Sarge.

443
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:31,240
All of you listen up.

444
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,720
Every one of you is a coward.

445
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:36,240
I give orders and none of you follow them.

446
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:38,600
Always chasing women.

447
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:40,360
Nothing ever gets done right.

448
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:42,920
Useless at work,
but when it comes to women,

449
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:45,160
you never miss.

450
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:48,440
This mission is off. I'll do it alone.

451
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:50,960
Go flirt. Go do whatever you want.

452
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,600
That's too much, Sarge.

453
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,960
I don't care what problem you've got,

454
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:57,640
but if you disrespect women like that,

455
00:37:57,720 --> 00:37:59,840
- you'll deal with me!
- Why? you wanna fight?

456
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:05,080
I can take all of you on. You want it?

457
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:07,480
- Shoot me then!
- Sure. You want it?

458
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:08,640
Akki.

459
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:11,960
- Akki, don't. Step back.
- No.

460
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:13,360
I'll pull the trigger for real.

461
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,160
- Sarge. Please. Don't.
- Please what, you bastard?

462
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:19,400
- Tangkuay. Tangkuay.
- Go be crazy somewhere else, Tangkuay.

463
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:29,040
You bunch of trash.

464
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:16,880
If I finish this whole bottle
and I'm still standing,

465
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:19,520
you go back and work with everyone.

466
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:20,760
Okay?

467
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,680
Hey. Whoa.

468
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:30,320
The plan to wipe out Tiangmon's online
gambling and call center scam network.

469
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:33,520
- This is the place.
- Follow the plan.

470
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:34,800
Dan. Juk.

471
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:36,720
<i>Cut the system and prep the bombs.</i>

472
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,920
<i>Kla. Tangkuay.</i>
<i>Infiltrate and clear the escape route.</i>

473
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,320
I've got a bad feeling about this.

474
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:44,400
Can I borrow your phone for a moment?

475
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:48,360
So you suspect
that I might be a mole, don't you?

476
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,360
- Come into this line.
- Moh.

477
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,400
- Sit down first.
- Moh.

478
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,520
What happened to you?

479
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:18,000
Where's Sarge?

480
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:19,640
I'm going to get back at him.

481
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:30,240
On the neck too.

482
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:33,680
- Oh, the face.
- Warn me first.

483
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:37,360
Powder. Dust. Powder.

484
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:41,800
I grab the arm.

485
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,280
Then throw you to the ground.

486
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,320
- Throw you down, then break the arm.
- Break the arm first.

487
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,560
All right.

488
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:47,880
Throw me down?

489
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:49,520
Just kidding.

490
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:53,000
- He already planned it.
- Easy. Easy. Easy.

491
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:57,880
Punch. Punch. Headlock.

492
00:40:57,960 --> 00:41:01,480
Grind the head. After that, pull the ear.
Something like that.

493
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:02,560
Go.

494
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:05,960
- Move. Move. Move.
- Okay.

495
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
